WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.768 --> 00:00:04.380
ALEKSEY SURKOV: I'll tell you
about Chrome Web Store today

00:00:04.380 --> 00:00:06.280
from various perspectives.

00:00:06.280 --> 00:00:08.510
So just to remind you
what Web Store is,

00:00:08.510 --> 00:00:14.090
this is Chrome Web Store--
chrome.google.com/webstore.

00:00:14.090 --> 00:00:16.790
How many of you have installed
at least one something

00:00:16.790 --> 00:00:18.400
from Web Store?

00:00:18.400 --> 00:00:18.900
Right.

00:00:18.900 --> 00:00:21.590
And how many of you
have uploaded something

00:00:21.590 --> 00:00:23.720
to Web Store as developers?

00:00:23.720 --> 00:00:26.290
OK, good, so about 50%.

00:00:26.290 --> 00:00:31.370
So the goal of my presentation
is to-- I actually

00:00:31.370 --> 00:00:32.500
have two goals, I guess.

00:00:32.500 --> 00:00:36.120
One goal is to give
you some idea why

00:00:36.120 --> 00:00:39.260
you might be interested in using
Web Store as a new distribution

00:00:39.260 --> 00:00:42.330
channel if you are not
doing this already.

00:00:42.330 --> 00:00:45.930
And the second goal is to give
some tips, or some things which

00:00:45.930 --> 00:00:48.300
are harder to find
in the documentation

00:00:48.300 --> 00:00:50.910
and at which might make
your app more effective

00:00:50.910 --> 00:00:53.750
and just bring you more users.

00:00:53.750 --> 00:00:58.170
So Web Store is supported on
all our desktop platforms-- Mac,

00:00:58.170 --> 00:00:59.530
Windows, Linux.

00:00:59.530 --> 00:01:01.855
We don't support any
mobile browsers yet,

00:01:01.855 --> 00:01:07.600
so don't try to open the
link from Android or iOS.

00:01:07.600 --> 00:01:09.560
What kind of content do
we have in Web Store?

00:01:09.560 --> 00:01:15.670
We really have three types
of items in Web Store.

00:01:15.670 --> 00:01:17.510
We have applications.

00:01:17.510 --> 00:01:20.010
And applications can
be hosted and packaged.

00:01:20.010 --> 00:01:21.850
So hosted applications
in Web Store

00:01:21.850 --> 00:01:24.300
are really just
links to websites.

00:01:24.300 --> 00:01:27.570
So if you have a website,
then making a host application

00:01:27.570 --> 00:01:30.660
in Web Store should take
not more than a few minutes.

00:01:30.660 --> 00:01:32.530
But the benefits
that you will have

00:01:32.530 --> 00:01:35.100
if you have this host
application in Web Store

00:01:35.100 --> 00:01:39.920
is that you will be able to get
user reviews, user feedback.

00:01:39.920 --> 00:01:43.300
For users, it will be
easier to find your website,

00:01:43.300 --> 00:01:45.050
your web application.

00:01:45.050 --> 00:01:48.800
They will be also able to read
some additional information,

00:01:48.800 --> 00:01:51.840
like description, and
see some screenshots.

00:01:51.840 --> 00:01:54.194
So I'll go in details
about that later.

00:01:54.194 --> 00:01:56.110
Packaged apps are something
slightly different

00:01:56.110 --> 00:01:59.280
from just hosted
apps, hosted websites.

00:01:59.280 --> 00:02:03.070
Packaged apps is, in
some way, a website

00:02:03.070 --> 00:02:04.970
which is packaged as a zip file.

00:02:04.970 --> 00:02:07.260
And at the install
time, it's downloaded

00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:09.520
to the user's machine so
that it can work offline

00:02:09.520 --> 00:02:11.210
without internet.

00:02:11.210 --> 00:02:14.920
So one of the biggest
advantages of packaged apps

00:02:14.920 --> 00:02:16.860
is that they are
offline by default.

00:02:16.860 --> 00:02:18.880
They just work without internet.

00:02:18.880 --> 00:02:24.290
Another advantage is that they
have access to various APIs

00:02:24.290 --> 00:02:26.930
which are not available
for just normal web apps.

00:02:26.930 --> 00:02:30.060
For example, they can interact
directly with a USB port.

00:02:30.060 --> 00:02:34.370
They can also use these
API [? pieces ?] [? just ?]

00:02:34.370 --> 00:02:35.614
directly.

00:02:35.614 --> 00:02:37.030
And they can do
many other things.

00:02:37.030 --> 00:02:38.821
They also run in their
own separate window,

00:02:38.821 --> 00:02:42.240
so on operating systems like
Linux or Mac or Windows,

00:02:42.240 --> 00:02:45.600
they just feel like
native applications.

00:02:45.600 --> 00:02:49.240
Extensions are things which
implement some functionality

00:02:49.240 --> 00:02:53.500
in the browser, in Chrome, which
doesn't exist there otherwise.

00:02:53.500 --> 00:02:56.260
They interact very
closely with the way

00:02:56.260 --> 00:02:58.030
Chrome renders the web pages.

00:02:58.030 --> 00:03:01.310
So one example of an
extension is-- obviously,

00:03:01.310 --> 00:03:04.680
AdBlocker is a good
example, or an extension

00:03:04.680 --> 00:03:07.350
which translates all the words
when you double click it,

00:03:07.350 --> 00:03:09.000
and many other
things you can do.

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:11.560
And themes is just a way to
add colors to your browser

00:03:11.560 --> 00:03:13.900
and maybe set some
background images to make

00:03:13.900 --> 00:03:18.200
the whole browser experience
more personalized.

00:03:18.200 --> 00:03:21.740
So we get, oftentimes, the
questions from developers.

00:03:21.740 --> 00:03:24.520
They are wondering how
the homepage of Web Store

00:03:24.520 --> 00:03:27.520
gets constructed
and what the way is

00:03:27.520 --> 00:03:30.520
to get to the top
of this home wall--

00:03:30.520 --> 00:03:33.182
the top of the home page.

00:03:33.182 --> 00:03:36.930
I really just wanted
to give you a view

00:03:36.930 --> 00:03:40.400
on how this wall
gets constructed

00:03:40.400 --> 00:03:43.740
and what kind of
content is shown here.

00:03:43.740 --> 00:03:46.890
So the first section and
the third section sections

00:03:46.890 --> 00:03:50.710
manually curated by a
Google merchandising team.

00:03:50.710 --> 00:03:54.500
So these are hand-picked apps.

00:03:54.500 --> 00:03:56.890
Google uses different
signals to decide

00:03:56.890 --> 00:03:59.130
which apps to promote here.

00:03:59.130 --> 00:04:01.276
The signals include
things like the apps

00:04:01.276 --> 00:04:03.950
should be high-quality apps.

00:04:03.950 --> 00:04:09.030
It should also have
some popularity already.

00:04:09.030 --> 00:04:12.777
So if you want Google to pick up
your app for a promotion here,

00:04:12.777 --> 00:04:15.360
you really need to invest into
your own marketing a little bit

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:16.290
first.

00:04:16.290 --> 00:04:21.440
It should probably use some
features of the platform

00:04:21.440 --> 00:04:24.040
to showcase the
platform in a good way.

00:04:24.040 --> 00:04:29.390
And it might be also a new
launch, an exclusive launch

00:04:29.390 --> 00:04:30.860
on the Chrome platform.

00:04:30.860 --> 00:04:33.360
We also have some
sections generated

00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:36.840
using machine learning
and algorithms.

00:04:36.840 --> 00:04:38.390
We have a personalized,
section which

00:04:38.390 --> 00:04:39.890
is different for every user.

00:04:39.890 --> 00:04:41.780
We try to select
stuff which is most

00:04:41.780 --> 00:04:43.720
relevant to the particular user.

00:04:43.720 --> 00:04:46.880
And we also have
just popular things.

00:04:46.880 --> 00:04:48.460
And then we have
this infinite wall

00:04:48.460 --> 00:04:50.899
at the bottom of
the homepage, which

00:04:50.899 --> 00:04:53.190
is a mixture of various
streams that I mentioned about.

00:04:56.890 --> 00:04:58.600
So publishing to
Web Store really

00:04:58.600 --> 00:05:01.090
involves three simple steps.

00:05:01.090 --> 00:05:03.510
If you want to
publish a hosted app

00:05:03.510 --> 00:05:05.552
and you already have a
website, then essentially,

00:05:05.552 --> 00:05:07.176
you don't need to
create your solution,

00:05:07.176 --> 00:05:08.530
because you already have one.

00:05:08.530 --> 00:05:11.630
You just to add a Chrome
manifest, upload to Web Store,

00:05:11.630 --> 00:05:15.200
add some promotional
information, and you're done.

00:05:15.200 --> 00:05:16.750
If you want to
make an extension,

00:05:16.750 --> 00:05:18.650
or if you want to
make a packaged app,

00:05:18.650 --> 00:05:21.730
you really need to use the
APIs that Chrome provides

00:05:21.730 --> 00:05:24.270
specifically for extensions
and packaged apps

00:05:24.270 --> 00:05:26.340
to use all the features.

00:05:26.340 --> 00:05:30.400
And let me zoom in a little bit
on what promotional information

00:05:30.400 --> 00:05:35.110
we require for publishing
and why it's important.

00:05:35.110 --> 00:05:39.940
So you need to give us things
like promotional images

00:05:39.940 --> 00:05:42.630
that we use to render
your apps in the wall.

00:05:42.630 --> 00:05:45.020
And these images should
be of high quality,

00:05:45.020 --> 00:05:49.260
because we don't really want
to show low-quality images

00:05:49.260 --> 00:05:50.510
at the top of the wall.

00:05:50.510 --> 00:05:52.750
So we have a manual curation
process for the images

00:05:52.750 --> 00:05:54.520
that you upload from Web Store.

00:05:54.520 --> 00:05:59.040
And if we think that image
is low-quality, or maybe just

00:05:59.040 --> 00:06:03.190
a blank rectangle
without any information,

00:06:03.190 --> 00:06:05.490
or a lot of small text--
there are some guidelines

00:06:05.490 --> 00:06:09.290
for that-- we mark
this image as not

00:06:09.290 --> 00:06:10.970
to be shown on the
top of the wall.

00:06:10.970 --> 00:06:15.360
And then your item, even if it's
a very good, high-quality item,

00:06:15.360 --> 00:06:17.910
it will not be able to show
up at the top of the wall.

00:06:17.910 --> 00:06:20.370
So it's really important to
have high-quality promotional

00:06:20.370 --> 00:06:20.870
images.

00:06:20.870 --> 00:06:23.070
It also attracts users.

00:06:23.070 --> 00:06:24.890
It's also important
to have, for details,

00:06:24.890 --> 00:06:27.250
screenshots which show
how your app works

00:06:27.250 --> 00:06:29.207
or how your extension works.

00:06:29.207 --> 00:06:31.540
And the detailed description--
we know from user studies

00:06:31.540 --> 00:06:34.620
that users really love
detailed descriptions.

00:06:34.620 --> 00:06:36.040
They love detailed information.

00:06:36.040 --> 00:06:40.250
They try to learn more before
deciding whether or not

00:06:40.250 --> 00:06:42.220
they want to install.

00:06:42.220 --> 00:06:43.820
They're really
cautious about this.

00:06:43.820 --> 00:06:45.340
They also read
reviews and ratings,

00:06:45.340 --> 00:06:49.940
so it's good to have
good reviews and ratings.

00:06:49.940 --> 00:06:52.490
It's especially important if
you want to monetize your app,

00:06:52.490 --> 00:06:55.160
if you want your users to pay.

00:06:55.160 --> 00:06:58.510
So for monetization, Web
Store offers multiple ways

00:06:58.510 --> 00:07:00.980
that you can monetize your app.

00:07:00.980 --> 00:07:07.450
The most straightforward way--
at the same time, probably

00:07:07.450 --> 00:07:13.110
the way to scare most users
from the very beginning--

00:07:13.110 --> 00:07:17.110
is to have a prepaid app
or a prepaid extension

00:07:17.110 --> 00:07:21.290
where the users need to
pay in order to install.

00:07:21.290 --> 00:07:24.964
So if you have an extension
or a packaged app,

00:07:24.964 --> 00:07:26.130
this will just work for you.

00:07:26.130 --> 00:07:29.550
Web Store will not let the
user download without paying.

00:07:29.550 --> 00:07:32.400
But if you have a hosted app,
which is essentially a website,

00:07:32.400 --> 00:07:36.070
you also need to interact with
the Google Web Store server

00:07:36.070 --> 00:07:38.840
to query whether the
particular user has paid

00:07:38.840 --> 00:07:40.870
for the particular
application, and then you

00:07:40.870 --> 00:07:43.060
can decide what kind of
UI you want to render.

00:07:43.060 --> 00:07:45.180
Maybe you want to tell
the user to upgrade,

00:07:45.180 --> 00:07:49.620
or maybe you can provide
some free functionality.

00:07:49.620 --> 00:07:51.320
You can also enable
a free trial, which

00:07:51.320 --> 00:07:56.480
means that your app will
be able to get installed

00:07:56.480 --> 00:08:00.280
without paying, but then you
can implement some functionality

00:08:00.280 --> 00:08:03.160
to check whether or not a
payment actually happened.

00:08:03.160 --> 00:08:05.120
And there may be
limits on functionality

00:08:05.120 --> 00:08:07.520
in the application.

00:08:07.520 --> 00:08:10.200
We also recently
launched in-app payments

00:08:10.200 --> 00:08:11.700
maybe a few months ago.

00:08:11.700 --> 00:08:15.730
In-app payments give you a
way to configure what kind

00:08:15.730 --> 00:08:18.230
of in-app products you want
to have in your extension

00:08:18.230 --> 00:08:19.730
or in your application.

00:08:19.730 --> 00:08:22.350
And then the code snippet
on the right side,

00:08:22.350 --> 00:08:24.220
if you have an extension
or a packaged app,

00:08:24.220 --> 00:08:26.790
that's really all you
need to do to query

00:08:26.790 --> 00:08:29.630
what kind of in-app our
products a particular user who

00:08:29.630 --> 00:08:33.330
is currently using your
product has purchased.

00:08:33.330 --> 00:08:35.770
And then you can also act
accordingly, maybe-- open

00:08:35.770 --> 00:08:38.900
some game level or enable
some functionality.

00:08:38.900 --> 00:08:41.220
You're also free to use
your own custom solution.

00:08:41.220 --> 00:08:44.430
We don't enforce
using specifically

00:08:44.430 --> 00:08:45.350
Web Store solutions.

00:08:45.350 --> 00:08:48.250
You can use anything you want.

00:08:48.250 --> 00:08:49.950
And you can also,
obviously, use ads

00:08:49.950 --> 00:08:53.800
just as you do it for websites.

00:08:53.800 --> 00:09:00.150
So this is a feature which
was just launched yesterday.

00:09:00.150 --> 00:09:03.630
Web Store format for
the manifest file

00:09:03.630 --> 00:09:06.360
supports internationalization
and localization

00:09:06.360 --> 00:09:07.380
to multiple languages.

00:09:07.380 --> 00:09:10.750
So you can say, here
is my title in English

00:09:10.750 --> 00:09:12.250
and my description in English.

00:09:12.250 --> 00:09:14.980
Here my title and description
in Chinese and German

00:09:14.980 --> 00:09:17.220
and every language
that you care about.

00:09:17.220 --> 00:09:19.620
In case you don't really
know how to translate,

00:09:19.620 --> 00:09:21.810
or you don't want to
deal with it yourself

00:09:21.810 --> 00:09:24.630
how to translate your
description and your app title

00:09:24.630 --> 00:09:26.380
to other languages,
is we now have

00:09:26.380 --> 00:09:30.350
this semi-automated process--
and you can find it now

00:09:30.350 --> 00:09:33.150
in your Chrome Web Store
Developer Dashboard--

00:09:33.150 --> 00:09:36.490
where you can actually use
the professional translations

00:09:36.490 --> 00:09:38.940
to request translations
for your listings.

00:09:38.940 --> 00:09:43.000
The prices are-- for most
languages it's $0.10 per word,

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:44.870
and the turnaround time
is less than a week.

00:09:44.870 --> 00:09:47.030
And we support 25 languages.

00:09:47.030 --> 00:09:52.010
And the good news is that
for all of you who are here

00:09:52.010 --> 00:09:56.160
listening to this talk, we
want to offer a refund up

00:09:56.160 --> 00:10:02.750
to $100 for all translations
that you make from Web Store

00:10:02.750 --> 00:10:03.910
by the end of this month.

00:10:03.910 --> 00:10:07.030
So you can just go
to the link there.

00:10:07.030 --> 00:10:09.640
It's also written
on the whiteboard.

00:10:09.640 --> 00:10:14.560
And the first 50 responses
will get free refunds

00:10:14.560 --> 00:10:17.128
for all translations
made from Web Store.

00:10:19.940 --> 00:10:23.510
Another thing which
developers often ask us about

00:10:23.510 --> 00:10:26.660
is why publishing an
app takes so much time,

00:10:26.660 --> 00:10:28.650
why it takes so long.

00:10:28.650 --> 00:10:32.100
And that's because we have an
app review process to fight

00:10:32.100 --> 00:10:34.510
malware, abuse, and
other bad things.

00:10:34.510 --> 00:10:36.580
Extensions, for example,
are very powerful,

00:10:36.580 --> 00:10:40.162
and they can do a very bad
things to the user's browser.

00:10:40.162 --> 00:10:41.870
They can steal all
the data, potentially,

00:10:41.870 --> 00:10:44.070
and we definitely don't
want this to happen.

00:10:44.070 --> 00:10:47.690
So we have a two-stage
review process.

00:10:47.690 --> 00:10:49.120
When you click the
Publish button,

00:10:49.120 --> 00:10:55.920
the app does not immediately
get available to all your users.

00:10:55.920 --> 00:10:57.120
There is some delay.

00:10:57.120 --> 00:10:59.980
And we use this delay
to first scan your item

00:10:59.980 --> 00:11:02.590
using automatic
malware-fighting pipeline.

00:11:02.590 --> 00:11:04.940
And the pipeline can say,
oh, the item is safe,

00:11:04.940 --> 00:11:05.940
and then we publish it.

00:11:05.940 --> 00:11:08.240
It can say, the
item is not safe.

00:11:08.240 --> 00:11:09.520
It's malware.

00:11:09.520 --> 00:11:10.980
And then we take it down.

00:11:10.980 --> 00:11:12.760
And then it can also
say, I don't know,

00:11:12.760 --> 00:11:15.740
but it looks suspicious.

00:11:15.740 --> 00:11:17.560
So then, if it
looks suspicious, we

00:11:17.560 --> 00:11:19.750
send it to manual
review process.

00:11:19.750 --> 00:11:22.100
And it can take slightly
more time in that case,

00:11:22.100 --> 00:11:26.210
so we have experts to look
at each particular item.

00:11:26.210 --> 00:11:30.720
So what's important here is
that, even though it's sounds

00:11:30.720 --> 00:11:33.410
a little bit scary,
most items get

00:11:33.410 --> 00:11:35.120
published within 60 minutes.

00:11:35.120 --> 00:11:38.380
And then it's very important
to monitor the email

00:11:38.380 --> 00:11:40.760
that you use to publish
items in Web Store,

00:11:40.760 --> 00:11:42.460
because Google
will use this email

00:11:42.460 --> 00:11:46.010
to send your notifications
about any problems which

00:11:46.010 --> 00:11:47.520
are happening with your items.

00:11:47.520 --> 00:11:49.930
And in some cases,
it's very effective

00:11:49.930 --> 00:11:53.190
to just appeal, or to
reply to the notification

00:11:53.190 --> 00:11:55.400
some sensible way,
and then the item

00:11:55.400 --> 00:11:57.380
can be restored
very quickly again.

00:11:59.951 --> 00:12:01.450
Another feature I
wanted to tell you

00:12:01.450 --> 00:12:05.610
about to in Web Store
is user feedback.

00:12:05.610 --> 00:12:08.170
So everybody knows that
it's important to listen

00:12:08.170 --> 00:12:10.410
to user feedback.

00:12:10.410 --> 00:12:14.690
We offer a feature
which helps to simplify

00:12:14.690 --> 00:12:16.300
interacting with your users.

00:12:16.300 --> 00:12:19.060
You just need to opt in from
your Developer Dashboard.

00:12:19.060 --> 00:12:21.380
And this two effects.

00:12:21.380 --> 00:12:24.090
First, the users will start
to see a link to a Support

00:12:24.090 --> 00:12:26.850
page in Web Store for your item.

00:12:26.850 --> 00:12:31.630
And when they go there, they
can leave bug reports or feature

00:12:31.630 --> 00:12:33.910
requests, or just ask questions.

00:12:33.910 --> 00:12:36.020
And on the other hand,
you as a developer

00:12:36.020 --> 00:12:39.960
will see a count of
unreplied feedback items,

00:12:39.960 --> 00:12:42.530
and you'll be able
to reply to them

00:12:42.530 --> 00:12:44.490
or just react to
them in some way.

00:12:47.590 --> 00:12:49.050
Another interesting
channel which

00:12:49.050 --> 00:12:50.710
was just launched
a couple of days

00:12:50.710 --> 00:12:54.670
ago is called Google
Play for Education.

00:12:54.670 --> 00:12:57.780
I want to tell you a
little bit more about this.

00:12:57.780 --> 00:12:59.280
Google Play for
Education is a place

00:12:59.280 --> 00:13:01.240
where Google Play team
and Chrome Web Store

00:13:01.240 --> 00:13:05.550
team combined their efforts to
make this product for teachers

00:13:05.550 --> 00:13:08.030
and their students
in the schools.

00:13:08.030 --> 00:13:14.830
So currently, it has
Android apps and Chrome apps

00:13:14.830 --> 00:13:18.560
which teachers can install
to their student's machines

00:13:18.560 --> 00:13:22.040
and use that for
educational purposes.

00:13:22.040 --> 00:13:25.660
So at this moment, we
just manually hand-picked

00:13:25.660 --> 00:13:28.650
a handful of Chrome
Web store apps

00:13:28.650 --> 00:13:31.430
and added them to Google
Play for Education.

00:13:31.430 --> 00:13:35.030
